=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
history</a> of=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/25418633.268044/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2lyZWQuY29tL3N0b3J5L2dhYi1oYWNrLWRhdGEtY=
nJlYWNoLWRkb3NlY3JldHMv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC3c212145" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">hilariou=
s</a>=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2541863=
3.268044/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwMjEvNi8yLzIyNDY0OTMwL2RvbmFsZC=
10cnVtcC1ibG9nLWZhY2Vib29rLXR3aXR0ZXItc29jaWFsLW1lZGlhLXBsYXRmb3Jt/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB574648d6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">failure</a> in the =E2=80=9Csocial media=
 for Trump=E2=80=9D category=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0but maybe you can. It is n=
ot a=C2=A0<em>sure thing</em>, in any case. Maybe it would work, maybe it w=
ouldn=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0When Twitter Inc. went public it had <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25418633.268044/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2=
VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMDk1MDEyMzE0MDAzMDMxL3R3d=
HItMTBrXzIwMTMxMjMxLmh0bSNJdGVtXzZfU0VMRUNURURfRklOQU5DSUFMX0RBVEE/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBfaf87506" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">never been profitable</a> and it was, yo=
u know, a real social network that people used. Maybe Twitter But Trump=C2=
=A0would immediately be profitable but boy I have some doubts.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand if Donald Trump launched a company t=
hat was like =E2=80=9CI am going to start a social media platform for Trump=
 fans,=E2=80=9D could he get people to=C2=A0<em>buy the stock</em>? I think=
 that two fundamental lessons of the last few years are:</p><ol style=3D"li=
st-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can get people to buy=C2=A0any<em>=C2=A0</em>s=
tock; and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Donald Trump can get peo=
ple to buy anything.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So if Donald Tru=
mp announced =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99m gonna do a social media company, buy =
some stock,=E2=80=9D people would buy some stock. And then he=E2=80=99d get=
 a lot of money.[1] And then if the social media platform did not end up be=
ing profitable =E2=80=94=C2=A0as I cannot imagine it would be! =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0then he would, uh, still have that money? And if the social media platfo=
rm did not end up being <em>launched</em> =E2=80=94=C2=A0if Trump and his c=
rack team of technologists just couldn=E2=80=99t actually build a well-func=
tioning online social network =E2=80=94=C2=A0then he would, uh, still have =
that money? And if there was no crack team of technologists at all, if nobo=
dy even=C2=A0<em>tried=C2=A0</em>to build the social media platform =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0then=C2=A0you see where I am going with this right?</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">The point is that if you launch a company with the goal o=
f making it profitable, you have to, like, have a workable business=C2=A0pl=
an and execute on it and deal with a million different operational complexi=
ties. If you launch a company with the goal of selling a lot of stock, you =
have to get people to trust you and give you their money. There is some ove=
rlap between those things! But they are different things!</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Now, there are some difficulties with doing an initial publi=
c offering that is like =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re gonna build a beautiful soci=
al network, trust me.=E2=80=9D But a third important lesson of the last few=
 years is:</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A03. SPACs!</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you go public by merging your private comp=
any with a special purpose acquisition company, then you can just make up w=
hatever you want and no one will check. No, I=E2=80=99m kidding, that is ve=
ry much not the law! But it is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/25418633.268044/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMTIvbWF5YmUtc3BhY3MtYXJlLXJlYWxseS1pcG9zP2NtcGlkPUJCR=
DEwMjEyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVy=
JnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTAyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBe03248a0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> maybe a little bit the law</a>? In particular, ther=
e is a view that pre-revenue private companies can go public via SPAC merge=
r and market themselves to investors using wildly optimistic projections of=
 their <em>future</em> revenue, and that if those projections do not come t=
rue they won=E2=80=99t get in trouble. Again, this is not quite true =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0talk to your lawyer before trying this! =E2=80=94=C2=A0but there i=
s an element of truth to it.=C2=A0If you are in the business of raising mon=
ey to fund a social media company that you haven=E2=80=99t built yet and pe=
rhaps never will, the SPAC format has a real appeal.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">Anyway, anyway, anyway, anyway, anyway, <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25418633.268044/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9=
BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTI4MjMyL3RtMjEzMDcyNG=
QxX2V4OTktMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf1ba684" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">anyway</a>:</p=
><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">PALM BEACH, FL -- October 20, 202=
1 -- Trump Media &amp; Technology Group and Digital World Acquisition Corp.=
 (NASDAQ: DWAC) have entered into a definitive merger agreement, providing =
for a business combination that will result in Trump Media &amp; Technology=
 Group becoming a publicly listed company, subject to regulatory and stockh=
older approval. The transaction values Trump Media &amp; Technology Group a=
t an initial enterprise value of $875 Million, with a potential additional =
earnout of $825 Million in additional shares (at the valuation they are gra=
nted) for a cumulative valuation of up to $1.7 Billion depending on the per=
formance of the stock price post-business combination. Trump Media &amp; Te=
chnology Group=E2=80=99s growth plans initially will be funded by DWAC=E2=
=80=99s cash in trust of $293 Million (assuming no redemptions).</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trump Media &amp; Technology Group's mission is to cr=
eate a rival to the liberal media consortium and fight back against the "Bi=
g Tech=E2=80=9D companies of Silicon Valley, which have used their unilater=
al power to silence opposing voices in America.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Trump Media &amp; Technology Group (=E2=80=9CTMTG=E2=80=9D) will soon =
be launching a social network, named "TRUTH Social." TRUTH Social is now av=
ailable for Pre-Order in the Apple App store. TRUTH Social plans to begin i=
ts Beta Launch for invited guests in November 2021. A nationwide rollout is=
 expected in the first quarter of 2022. Those who are interested in joining=
 TRUTH Social may now visit www.truthsocial.com to sign up for the invite l=
ist.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">President Donald J. Trump, the Chairma=
n of TMTG, stated, =E2=80=9CI created TRUTH Social and TMTG to stand up to =
the tyranny of Big Tech. We live in a world where the Taliban has a huge pr=
esence on Twitter, yet your favorite American President has been silenced. =
This is unacceptable. I am excited to send out my first TRUTH on TRUTH Soci=
al very soon. TMTG was founded with a mission to give a voice to all. I'm e=
