<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Deals</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah okay I kind of like this:</p><blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At Partners Group Holding AG, =E2=80=
=9Cdeal=E2=80=9D is a four-letter word.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dav=
id Layton, the Swiss firm=E2=80=99s chief executive, banned the term at a g=
lobal town hall meeting in early June.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Neve=
r mind that as a private-equity firm with $119 billion in assets,=C2=A0<a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25418633.268044/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9tYXJrZXQtZGF0YS9xdW90ZXMvQ0gvWFNXWC9QR0hO/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBff059c36" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Partners Group</a>=C2=A0exists to =
do=E2=80=A6deals.=E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Layton, 40 y=
ears old, says he banned the word because he is trying to get his colleague=
s to shift from a transactional mind-set to one he calls =E2=80=9Cindustria=
l.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two decades ago, Mr. Layton say=
s, the buyout business was a $700 billion industry in which firms made big =
money with a simple formula: buy companies using a large amount of debt, ma=
ke some cosmetic changes and sell them off. These days, it=E2=80=99s an $8 =
trillion industry, and if firms want to make the double-digit returns their=
 investors expect, they have to think like entrepreneurs, he says.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe want to act like founders, not financie=
rs,=E2=80=9D Mr. Layton says. =E2=80=9CDo our customers love us? Is our pro=
duct resonating?=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He says the word =
=E2=80=9Cdeal=E2=80=9D reduces the ownership of a company=E2=80=94which has=
 executives, employees, a strategy and a mission=E2=80=94to a one-time even=
t. He wants the employees of his firm to act like they are owners of busine=
sses, not merely the doers of deals.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prefer=
red vocabulary includes =E2=80=9Cstewardship, governance, strategy, culture=
, entrepreneurship, operational excellence and sustainability,=E2=80=9D he =
says. Some employees have resorted to using the word =E2=80=9Cinvestment=E2=
=80=9D as a substitute for the banned word.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">If you say the d-word you get fined. I assume that this is pa=
rtly a cutesy marketing gimmick but you know what, it=E2=80=99s a competiti=
ve world, a little cutesy marketing doesn=E2=80=99t hurt.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">But, also, I used to be an investment banker. Investment ban=
kers do deals. Fine. But I was in a weird derivatives banking group that so=
rt of put on airs, and we didn=E2=80=99t like to say =E2=80=9Cdeal,=E2=80=
=9D we said =E2=80=9Ctrade.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0We=E2=80=99d go meet with a compa=
ny and our regular banking colleagues would pitch a deal and then we=E2=80=
=99d pitch a trade. A =E2=80=9Cdeal=E2=80=9D is more short-term and transac=
tional than, uh, =E2=80=9Cstewardship,=E2=80=9D but a =E2=80=9Ctrade=E2=80=
=9D is even more short-term and transactional and arm=E2=80=99s-length and =
zero-sum and adversarial. Honestly I think it warped me for life? Even now =
I read about mergers with some weird financial structuring and think =E2=80=
=9Cthat=E2=80=99s=C2=A0a good trade.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s not a good trade=
! It=E2=80=99s a perpetual commitment to bind together two companies with a=
ll sorts of social and operational issues involved in integrating them. But=
, also, tax structuring. I have become a person who appreciates financial s=
tructuring and a certain amount of =E2=80=A6=C2=A0trickery? gimmickry? =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0and I suspect that the vocabulary may have had something to do =
with it.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=
=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
